---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="System"
	description="How OrgOps works: a small runtime where typed events drive agents and explicit commands, with auditability and control."
>
	<header class="hero">
		<h1>System</h1>
		<p class="lede">
			OrgOps is a small, explicit runtime for agent-driven operations: events in, actions out — with auditability and
			control.
		</p>
	</header>

	<section class="grid">
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Events as the backbone</h2>
			<p>
				Work is represented as typed events. That makes workflows inspectable, replayable, and easier to integrate.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Agents with guardrails</h2>
			<p>
				Agents operate inside channels, follow coordination rules, and emit structured outputs instead of hidden side
				effects.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Skills, not plugins</h2>
			<p>
				Capabilities are packaged as skills: scripts + event schemas + conventions. Keep the core small; extend at the
				edges.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>What you get</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Traceability:</strong> see what happened, when, and why.</li>
			<li><strong>Safety:</strong> scoped secrets, explicit commands, and auditable actions.</li>
			<li><strong>Velocity:</strong> automate the boring parts without losing accountability.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>A tiny example</h2>
		<p>
			A human asks for a deploy in a channel. An agent responds with a structured command request instead of running
			shell commands silently.
		</p>
		<pre class="code"><code>{`{
  "type": "channel.command.requested",
  "payload": {
    "command": "deploy.preview",
    "args": { "service": "api", "ref": "main" }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
		<p>
			That command is visible in the event log, can be approved/denied, and produces a success/failure event.
		</p>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.lede {
		max-width: 70ch;
		color: rgb(var(--muted));
	}
	.section {
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
	}
	.code {
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
		padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
		border-radius: 1rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--black), 10%);
		background: rgba(var(--black), 2%);
		overflow-x: auto;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}
	:global(html[data-theme='dark']) .code {
		border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 14%);
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 6%);
	}
	.grid {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
	}
	.card {
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 1rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--black), 10%);
		background: rgba(var(--black), 2%);
	}
	:global(html[data-theme='dark']) .card {
		border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 14%);
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 6%);
	}
	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
